Thanks Frankie!!!  Yeah it's a good thing she has her mother's good look   Just give them more exposure and in time they will
soon enough I can get my girls to do the same. Baby steps for now

Take it slow Vinni and they will adapt    You have to realize that MÃ©lissa has help me prep the deer head of my last 2 bucks without any issues.... she found the experience quite fascinating and looks forward to my next one  Heck.... she knows how to clean a partridge too     Showed her that at an early age   so holding a fish is a breeze for her now  Jacques
The way she is holding it, it looks like a perch shaped Harmonica. Glad to see the youths out in the fresh air enjoying their heritage.   Art
Yeah Art.... A big Harmonica   Next for her, she wants to go pass her security firearm course so she can come along hunting with me
In time

Good for her I am glad to hear that. I have a firstmate for the 28ft boat who's 17 year old niece is the 2ndmate and she is going to get her boaters license this winter so she can run the boat. This fall she had to have cataracts removed from both eyes and now can see the buoys and channel marks well enough for me to feel comfortable letting her drive.   Art
Awesome Art   Them's are the best age to learn the ropes
OK.... Good luck to all participants!!!

Thanks to Vince and his Daughters for adding a little winter fun to the forum... that and the nice swag !!!  Toque and rattlin rap with Snap On logo.. a couple worm harness and a BIG jar of Bigugli's Salsa !!  Can't forget those nice crayon drawings either....  Thanks Girls (you too Vince!)
